(26, 'Guidelines for Third Party Data Requests', 'guidelines-for-third-party-data-requests', '<h1><strong>Turvy Guidelines for Third-Party Data Requests and Service of Legal Documents</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following guidelines are intended to inform private parties, including civil litigants and criminal defendants, about the legal process for seeking records from Turvy. These are merely guidelines, and this information may change at any&nbsp;time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These guidelines apply to non-law enforcement requests. For law enforcement requests, we recommend browsing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.uber.com/legal/data-requests/guidelines-for-law-enforcement-united-states\">Guidelines for Law Enforcement&nbsp;Authorities</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is Turvy, and what records do we have?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Turvy is a technology company that has developed an app that connects users (riders) with third party transportation providers. More details about our services are available&nbsp;<a href=\"https://help.uber.com/\">here</a>. We store, use, and maintain information as described in our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.uber.com/legal/privacy/users\">Privacy Statements</a>&nbsp;and our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.uber.com/legal/global/privacy\">Terms of&nbsp;Use</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Where does Turvy accept the service of legal documents?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We generally require that all legal documents (including complaints and subpoenas) be served on our registered agent for service of process. The name and current contact information for the registered agent in each state are available online&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ct.wolterskluwer.com/sop-locations\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our registered agent will accept service only if the entity to whom the document is directed matches the entity&#39;s name registered with the Secretary of State (e.g., &ldquo;Turvy Pty Ltd&rdquo;). Our agent is authorised to accept service on behalf of that entity. Our acceptance of the legal process does not waive any legal objections we may have and may raise in&nbsp;response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents should be directed to &ldquo;Turvy Pty Ltd.&rdquo; We generally require that all legal documents be served at the following address: 14/19A Market Street, Wollongong NSW 2500, Australia. Our acceptance of the legal process does not waive any legal objections we may have and may raise in&nbsp;response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What legal process does Turvy require before producing data to private parties?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia Requests</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We generally require a valid subpoena issued by applicable law before processing private requests for information. We need non-law enforcement subpoenas to be served through our registered agent for the service of the process. The name and current contact information for the registered agent in each state are available online&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ct.wolterskluwer.com/sop-locations\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our registered agent will accept service only if the entity to whom the request is directed matches the entity&#39;s name registered with the ASIC &nbsp;(e.g., &ldquo;Turvy Pty Ltd&rdquo;). Our agent is authorised to accept service on behalf of that entity. Our acceptance of the legal process does not waive any legal objections we may have and may raise in&nbsp;response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Non-Australia Requests</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Non-Australia requests should be directed to &ldquo;Turvy Pty Ltd.&rdquo; We generally require a valid request issued by applicable law before processing private requests for information. We need submissions to be served by registered mail to the following address: 14/19A Market Street, Wollongong NSW 2500, Australia. Our acceptance of the legal process does not waive any legal objections we may have and may raise in response to the&nbsp;request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What form of requests does Turvy require, and how are requests processed?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We review each subpoena or data request for facial and substantive validity and will reject bids that are not facially and substantively valid. We require recommendations to be narrowly tailored and will reject overly broad, vague, or unduly burdensome bids. Before making a request, please check to see if the information sought is publicly&nbsp;available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To make sure your request is valid, we ask for the&nbsp;following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A sufficiently narrow/defined period and the specific data requested within that period</li>\r\n	<li>A specific identifying reference (i.e., you must uniquely identify a user or driver/partner, ideally by more than just a&nbsp;name)</li>\r\n	<li>Your contact information (i.e., name and email address and phone&nbsp;number)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When we determine that we are required by law to disclose data, we will search for and disclose data that we can reasonably locate and&nbsp;retrieve.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: We will not respond to emergency requests received from non-law enforcement officials. Non-law enforcement officials aware of an emergency should immediately and directly contact local law&nbsp;enforcement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Does Turvy provide a certificate of authentication or expert testimony?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We may provide a certification from the custodian of our records but are generally not able to provide in-person or expert witness&nbsp;testimony.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\" target=\"_self\">Return to Legal</a></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://di3g1t698x49r.cloudfront.net/arrow.png\" style=\"height:35px; width:46px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(27, 'Third Party Insurance', 'third-party-insurance', '<h1>Third-Party Property Damage Motor Vehicle Insurance Policy</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Driver-partners must hold and maintain a valid third party property damage or comprehensive motor vehicle insurance policy that protects against property damage to third parties when driving&nbsp;using the Turvy&nbsp;apps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\" target=\"_self\">Return to Legal</a></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://di3g1t698x49r.cloudfront.net/arrow.png\" style=\"height:35px; width:46px\" /></a></h2>'),
(30, 'Health General Terms and Conditions', 'health-general-terms-and-conditions', '<h1><strong>Turvy Health Product Addendum to the Turvy for Business General Terms and Conditions &ndash; Australia</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company identified within this sign-up page (&ldquo;Company&rdquo;) at this moment accepts and agrees to this Turvy Health Product Addendum (&ldquo;Product Addendum&rdquo;) to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.uber.com/legal/en/document/?name=uber-for-business-dashboard-terms&amp;country=australia&amp;lang=en-au\">Turvy for Business General Terms and Conditions</a>&nbsp;(&ldquo;General Terms&rdquo;), which constitutes a legally binding agreement by and between Company and Turvy Pty Ltd, an Australian company registered in New South Wales (ABN 75 622 611 894), registered at 14/19A, Market&nbsp;Street, Wollongong&nbsp;NSW 2500, Australia (&ldquo;Turvy&rdquo;). Capitalised terms used but not otherwise defined herein shall have the meaning ascribed to such terms in the General Terms. In the event of any conflict between the terms of the General Terms and this Product Addendum, the terms of this Product Addendum shall govern. This Product Addendum sets forth the terms a Company may utilise the Dashboard to enable Turvy Health. The company&rsquo;s use of Turvy Health is subject to this Product Addendum, as it may be modified or updated by Turvy as outlined in the General&nbsp;Terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Definitions.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following terms, as may be used only in this Product Addendum, shall have the meanings set forth below: &ldquo;Active User&rdquo; means an individual with an active personal Turvy user account for the Turvy Service, the creation of which requires (i) registering with Turvy and (ii) accepting the End User Terms. &ldquo;Turvy Health User&rdquo; means an Active User or Guest User. &ldquo;Turvy Health User Data&rdquo; has the meaning outlined in section 2.2. &ldquo;Designated Recipient&rdquo; means an individual authorised by a Turvy Health User to provide information to Turvy and receive notifications from Turvy, including but not limited to SMS messages, regarding such Turvy Health User&rsquo;s trip. &ldquo;Guest User&rdquo; means an individual who is not an Active User. &ldquo;Turvy Health&rdquo; means the Turvy for Business product that, in connection with Turvy&rsquo;s technology systems, enables the Company to request rides on behalf of the Company&rsquo;s customers, clients, or other authorised individuals using the Turvy Health&nbsp;product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Provision of Services to Company</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.1. Access to Services.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon executing this Product Addendum, Turvy will use commercially reasonable efforts to enable the Company to access Turvy Health via the Dashboard. In addition to the Dashboard features described in the General Terms, the Dashboard will allow Company to (a) request rides on behalf of Turvy Health Users and (b) view a monthly statement setting forth trips requested on Turvy Health Users. Company expressly acknowledges and agrees that (i) any transportation services provided to Turvy Health Users are provided neither by Turvy nor by Company, but by independent third-party transportation providers; and (ii) Company is acting solely as an administrative agent of Turvy Health Users to relay requests for transportation services on behalf of Turvy Health Users. The company acknowledges that any Administrator utilising Monthly Billing will incur User Charges to the account of the Company and not to the applicable Turvy Health User&#39;s account or credit&nbsp;card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.2. Active Users; Guest Users; Designated Recipients.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(a)&nbsp;Before requesting the Turvy Service on behalf of any Turvy Health User, Company shall obtain from the Turvy Health User and submit to Turvy the following information concerning such Central User: (i) first and last name; (ii) active mobile phone or landline number; (iii) pick-up and drop-off location; and (iv) pick-up time and other optional trip-related data (e.g. billing code, room number, trip purpose, and message to driver-partner) (&ldquo;Turvy Health User Data&rdquo;), to permit Turvy to confirm whether such Turvy Health User is an Active User or a Guest User. The company shall ensure that all data provided to Turvy is accurate and complete. Turvy shall not be liable to Company, any Turvy Health User or any other party concerning inaccurate or incomplete data supplied by&nbsp;Company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(b)&nbsp;Company shall be solely responsible for contacting, or facilitating contact with, any Guest User for whom Company requests the Turvy Services. Turvy shall have no responsibility for getting or providing messaging under this Product Addendum to any individual who is not an Active&nbsp;User.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(c)&nbsp;Company acknowledges that any Turvy Health User may be suspended or banned from use of the Turvy Service due to future or past violations of the End User Terms of Turvy&rsquo;s Community Guidelines, available at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/community-guidelines\">https://www.turvy.net/community-guidelines</a>&nbsp;as may be updated by Turvy from time to time, (&quot;Violations&quot;) and that in those circumstances Turvy shall have no obligation or liability related to a Turvy Health User that is unable to utilise the Turvy Services. (d) The company may provide Turvy with the name and phone number of Designated recipients (s) for Turvy (at Turvy&rsquo;s sole discretion) to provide notifications and detailed trip information, including real-time trip status, regarding a Turvy Health User&rsquo;s trip to such Designated Recipient, including via SMS. Turvy shall not be liable to Company, any Central User, any Designated Recipient, or any other party concerning inaccurate or incomplete information supplied by Company related to any Designated&nbsp;Recipient.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.3. Restrictions.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Company agrees to and to cause all Turvy Health Users to use the Turvy Service and Turvy App solely as outlined in this Product Addendum, the General Terms, and the End User Terms; provided, however, that in the event of a conflict between this Product Addendum, the General Terms and the End User Terms concerning Company or any authorised Turvy Health User or an Administrator employing Monthly Billing with the Turvy Service, the terms of this Product Addendum shall control, followed by the General Terms, then the End User Terms. Turvy reserves the right to suspend the Company&rsquo;s use or any Administrator&rsquo;s use of Turvy Health and the Corporate Account for violations of this Product Addendum, the General Terms or the End User&nbsp;Terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2.4. Booking requirements.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The company represents and warrants that it is solely responsible for: (i) deciding an Active User or Guest User&rsquo;s eligibility to use Turvy Health; (ii) requesting the form of transport that is most suitable for that person; and (iii) deciding how transportation options are made available to that person. In addition, Company is prohibited from using the Dashboard and Turvy Health product to transport Active Users or Guest Users: (a) as a substitute for ambulatory services; (b) for any purpose where emergency or non-emergency patient transport is more appropriate; or (c) who the Company, in its discretion, considers that the person is high risk. The company ensures that its practices are current with public health information and updates related to COVID for the city and state. It is booking trips using the Dashboard and Turvy Health&nbsp;products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Fees and Payments</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.1. Service Fees and User Charges.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(a)&nbsp;Company will pay a monthly fee for the use of Turvy Health (a &ldquo;Service Fee&rdquo;), which shall equal the amount set forth during the account creation or as otherwise assessed by Turvy after providing at least thirty (30) days prior written notice of such fee to the Company. The Service Fee is exclusive of any GST. If GST is payable on the supply for which the Service Fee is considered, the Company agrees to pay an additional amount equal to the GST while the Service Fee is&nbsp;payable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(b)&nbsp;Company shall pay all User Charges Turvy properly assesses to Company for its use of Turvy Health. Such User Charges shall be paid for through the payment card associated with the Corporate Account unless Company participates in Monthly Billing. The Company shall pay such User Charges by section 5 of the General Terms. The company acknowledges and agrees that (i) the Company makes payment of User Charges on behalf of Turvy Health Users for transportation or other services that Turvy Health Users obtain through the use of the Turvy Services; and (ii) the User Charges are not a consideration for any service provided by&nbsp;Turvy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(c)&nbsp;Unless expressly stated otherwise in this Product Addendum, all amounts payable or consideration to be provided under this Product Addendum are exclusive of GST. If GST is payable on any supply made under this Product Addendum by Turvy, for which the consideration is not expressly stated to include GST, Company agrees to pay Turvy an additional amount equal to the GST at the same time that the review for the supply, or the first part of the consideration for the store (as the case may be), is to be&nbsp;provided.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.2. Billing Options.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(a)&nbsp;Under section 5 of the General Terms, Turvy may, in its sole discretion, elect to qualify Company to participate in Monthly&nbsp;Billing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(b)&nbsp;If Company does not participate in Monthly Billing, (i) User Charges incurred in connection with this Product Addendum shall be paid through the payment card associated with the Corporate Account; and (ii) Turvy shall charge Company for Service Fees incurred during each calendar month of the Term in which Monthly Billing was not utilised (each a &ldquo;Service Fee Invoice&rdquo;). All fees under each Service Fee Invoice shall become due and payable upon the issuance of such Service Fee&nbsp;Invoice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.3. Non-payment.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Turvy reserves the right to immediately charge the Company card if any Monthly Statement has not been paid as of the applicable due date. Turvy reserves the right to suspend the Company&rsquo;s account immediately and suspend any or all Monthly Billing in the event of any unpaid fees by the Company due to past due Monthly Statements (as applicable), an invalid card on the Corporate Account or a rejected Company card transaction. Turvy further reserves the right to pursue any remedies available to it under applicable law, including reporting the Company to appropriate credit reporting agencies, in the event of any unpaid fees hereunder. After full payment of late fees, re-establishing the Corporate Account shall be at Turvy&#39;s&nbsp;discretion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Privacy and Data Security</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>4.1. Lawfulness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Company agrees to inform and have an applicable legal basis to Process Personal Data and, where necessary, obtain consent from each Turvy Health User: (i) to provide Turvy Health User Data to Turvy; (ii) for Turvy to provide Company and any Designated Recipients with detailed information on, and real-time trip status of, the rides charged to Company&#39;s Corporate Account; and (iii) to receive short message services (&ldquo;SMS&rdquo;) and emails from Turvy, and for Turvy to otherwise contact each Turvy Health User to provide the Turvy Service or to provide any communications under the General Terms and this Product&nbsp;Addendum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4.2. Restrictions.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Turvy shall Process the Turvy Health User Data solely for the purposes described in this Product Addendum and the General&nbsp;Terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4.3. Damages.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Damages arising from the Company&rsquo;s breach of this &ldquo;Privacy and Data Security&rdquo; section shall not be subject to the limits of liability outlined in the General&nbsp;Terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. Effect of Termination.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>All outstanding payment obligations and sections 3-5 shall survive the termination of this Product&nbsp;Addendum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Warranty.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to the warranties outlined in the General Terms, Company represents and warrants that Company has obtained rights, permission and legally adequate consent from Central Users (a) to share such Central User&rsquo;s data with Turvy, (b) to receive SMS messages from Turvy in connection with Turvy Health and the Turvy Service; and (c) for Turvy to provide Company and any Designated Recipients with detailed trip information, including real-time trip status, for the rides charged to Company&rsquo;s account. In addition to the warranties outlined in the General Terms, Company represents and warrants that Company has obtained the rights, permission and legally adequate consent from Designated Recipients (i) to share such Designated Recipient&rsquo;s data with Turvy and (ii) to receive SMS messages from Turvy in connection with Turvy Health and the Turvy Service or to provide any communications under this Product Addendum. The company acknowledges that it may elect to utilise the Dashboard to request the Turvy Service and provide access to Monthly Billing on behalf of Guest Users. Any such election is at Company&#39;s sole discretion, and, in addition to Company&rsquo;s indemnity obligations under the General Terms, Company, therefore, will indemnify, defend and hold harmless Turvy, its Affiliates and their directors, officers, employees and agents against all claims, damages, losses and expenses (including reasonable attorney&#39;s fees) concerning any third-party claim arising out of or related to the use of the Turvy Service by any Guest User. Damages arising from the Company&rsquo;s breach of this &ldquo;Warranty&rdquo; section shall not be subject to the limits of liability outlined in the General&nbsp;Terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\" target=\"_self\">Return to Legal</a></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://di3g1t698x49r.cloudfront.net/arrow.png\" style=\"height:35px; width:46px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
(31, 'Driver to Hero Data-Sharing Policy', 'driver-to-hero-data-sharing-policy', '<h1><strong>Which information does Turvy share with your Hero?</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To help you set up your account, you may have shared personal information like your driver&rsquo;s license. To help manage your account, your Hero may need to access some of your account details. This page explains which information is shared by Turvy and&nbsp;why.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>First name, last name, and profile photo</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your name and profile photo are used to identify your&nbsp;account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Heroes can also edit basic personal details, such as your name and phone number if they need to correct mistakes in your&nbsp;account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Phone number</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Hero may contact you by phone to help set up your account and inform you about important updates to your&nbsp;account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Product and city of operation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The product refers to the type of Turvy product you use to provide services, such as ridesharing and food&nbsp;deliveries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During account setup, your Hero may enter the city&rsquo;s name, where you operate and your product (how you make a living using the Turvy&nbsp;app).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Along with your city of operation, the product determines which documents are needed to&nbsp;start.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Required documents, account status, and activation date</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Hero helps you provide Turvy with any required documents for driving. They may add photos of those documents to your account with your permission unless you prefer to add them&nbsp;yourself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Hero needs to review all of the documents Turvy requires before you start driving and, once they are submitted, determine whether these documents are rejected for any reason. After they have been submitted to Turvy, your Hero will not have access to your&nbsp;records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Trip count and date of the last trip</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Hero keeps track of the number of trips you complete to determine whether you reach specific performance&nbsp;goals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to stop sharing these details with your Hero,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://help.uber.com/partners/article/i-want-to-delete-my-account?nodeId=55ae2bb5-b102-4ab0-9ed3-32f4db95f0e5\">delete</a>&nbsp;your Partner-driver account and set up your own new Partner-driver&nbsp;account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\" target=\"_self\">Return to Legal</a></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.turvy.net/legal-1\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://di3g1t698x49r.cloudfront.net/arrow.png\" style=\"height:35px; width:46px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
